            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.25.33g"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">74-1    Aly Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">33<del/><add>g</add></fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>An Owl, Sitting on a Branch</figDesc>
                        <p>1866</p>
                    </figure>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">HENRY HOLT AND COMPANY, INC.</hi> â€¢ <hi rend="italics">Publishers</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        383 <hi rend="caps">MADISON AVENUE...NEW YORK  17, N. Y.</hi>
                        <lb/>
                
                    <hi rend="caps">GENERAL BOOKS
                        <lb/>
                    TEXTBOOKS
                        <lb/>
                    MAGAZINES</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    
                    <hi rend="italics">College Department</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>November 26, 1957</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Professor John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Department of English</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>University of Missouri</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Professor Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>It was extremely thoughtful of you to write as you did about the recent call of our Missouri representative, Alan McDonald. Such a letter as yours means a great deal to us, and it is heart-warming to know when a representative, especially a first-year man, is leaving a good impression of the house of Holt.</p>
                
                <p>He has written me with the greatest enthusiasm of his talk with you, and I am certain he will always remember the warm reception you gave him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Cordially yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Alden H. Clark</signed>
                
                    <signed>Alden H. Clark
                    Vice President</signed>
                    
                    <note>AHC/cb</note>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="recipient">Getting aquainted
                with <unclear>Holts</unclear> !</note> 
                
            </div1>
